{
  "text": "In the time-course study of SaOS-2 cells shown in Fig. 2 , both D2 mRNA and D2 activity were increased by (Bu) 2 cAMP (10 Ϫ3 m) and forskolin (10 Ϫ5 m) within 3 h and reached peak levels at 6 h. The rapid increase in D2 mRNA and D2 activity by the cAMP-elevating agent is in agreement with the results obtained using cultured rat astrocytes [CITATION_1] and cultured rat pineal gland [CITATION_2] . These results indicate that D2 expression is pretranslationally stimulated through a cAMP-mediated pathway.",
  "correct_citation": {
